{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "checkit-grpc-collection",
    "name": "CheckIt gRPC",
    "description": "Complete set of **all gRPC RPCs** exposed by this repo (there are no REST HTTP routes).\n\n| # | Service | Method | Server variable |\n|---|---------|--------|-----------------|\n| 1 | user.v1.UserService | **CreateUser** | `{{user_grpc_url}}` |\n| 2 | user.v1.UserService | **GetUserById** | `{{user_grpc_url}}` |\n| 3 | wallet.v1.WalletService | **CreateWallet** | `{{wallet_grpc_url}}` |\n| 4 | wallet.v1.WalletService | **GetWallet** | `{{wallet_grpc_url}}` |\n| 5 | wallet.v1.WalletService | **CreditWallet** | `{{wallet_grpc_url}}` |\n| 6 | wallet.v1.WalletService | **DebitWallet** | `{{wallet_grpc_url}}` |\n\n**Setup:** Import protos from `packages/proto/proto` (add that folder as a **proto import path**, then select `user/v1/user.proto` for user requests and `wallet/v1/wallet.proto` for wallet requests—or your Postman version’s equivalent). Use **plaintext** gRPC (no TLS) for local dev.\n\n**Flow:** Start **wallet** then **user** (`pnpm dev:wallet`, `pnpm dev:user`). Select the **CheckIt local** environment. Run **CreateUser** first; its **Tests** script saves `user.id` into `user_id` (environment + collection). Then run the rest in any order; wallet calls need `user_id` set.\n\n**Note:** CreateUser uses a unique email per run (`postman-{{$timestamp}}@example.com`) so you are less likely to hit `ALREADY_EXISTS` when re-running.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    {
      "key": "user_grpc_url",
      "value": "grpc://localhost:50051"
    },
    {
      "key": "wallet_grpc_url",
      "value": "grpc://localhost:50052"
    },
    {
      "key": "user_id",
      "value": ""
    },
    {
      "key": "proto_import_path",
      "value": "packages/proto/proto",
      "type": "string"
    }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "UserService (user_grpc_url)",
      "description": "Protobuf: `packages/proto/proto/user/v1/user.proto`. Service `user.v1.UserService`.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "1. CreateUser",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "function parseBody() {",
                  "  try { return pm.response.json(); } catch (e1) {}",
                  "  try { return JSON.parse(pm.response.text()); } catch (e2) {}",
                  "  return null;",
                  "}",
                  "const body = parseBody();",
                  "if (body && body.user && body.user.id) {",
                  "  const id = body.user.id;",
                  "  pm.environment.set('user_id', id);",
                  "  pm.collectionVariables.set('user_id', id);",
                  "  console.log('Saved user_id to environment + collection:', id);",
                  "} else {",
                  "  console.warn('No user.id in response; set user_id manually for wallet calls.');",
                  "}"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [],
            "body": {
              "mode": "grpc",
              "grpc": {
                "service": "user.v1.UserService",
                "method": "CreateUser",
                "message": "{\n  \"email\": \"postman-{{$timestamp}}@example.com\",\n  \"name\": \"Postman User\"\n}"
              }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{user_grpc_url}}"
            },
            "description": "Creates a user; **Tests** tab saves `user.id` into `user_id`."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "2. GetUserById",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [],
            "body": {
              "mode": "grpc",
              "grpc": {
                "service": "user.v1.UserService",
                "method": "GetUserById",
                "message": "{\n  \"userId\": \"{{user_id}}\"\n}"
              }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{user_grpc_url}}"
            },
            "description": "Requires `user_id` (run CreateUser first or paste a UUID)."
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "WalletService (wallet_grpc_url)",
      "description": "Protobuf: `packages/proto/proto/wallet/v1/wallet.proto`. Service `wallet.v1.WalletService`. User must exist (wallet service calls user service on CreateWallet).",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "3. CreateWallet",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [],
            "body": {
              "mode": "grpc",
              "grpc": {
                "service": "wallet.v1.WalletService",
                "method": "CreateWallet",
                "message": "{\n  \"userId\": \"{{user_id}}\",\n  \"idempotencyKey\": \"postman-create-1\"\n}"
              }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{wallet_grpc_url}}"
            },
            "description": "Idempotent per `(userId, idempotencyKey)`. Change `idempotencyKey` for a second distinct create attempt."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "4. GetWallet",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [],
            "body": {
              "mode": "grpc",
              "grpc": {
                "service": "wallet.v1.WalletService",
                "method": "GetWallet",
                "message": "{\n  \"userId\": \"{{user_id}}\"\n}"
              }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{wallet_grpc_url}}"
            },
            "description": "Returns balance in minor units."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "5. CreditWallet",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [],
            "body": {
              "mode": "grpc",
              "grpc": {
                "service": "wallet.v1.WalletService",
                "method": "CreditWallet",
                "message": "{\n  \"userId\": \"{{user_id}}\",\n  \"amountMinorUnits\": 1000,\n  \"idempotencyKey\": \"postman-credit-1\"\n}"
              }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{wallet_grpc_url}}"
            },
            "description": "Credits minor units. Same `idempotencyKey` + amount replays safely."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "6. DebitWallet",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [],
            "body": {
              "mode": "grpc",
              "grpc": {
                "service": "wallet.v1.WalletService",
                "method": "DebitWallet",
                "message": "{\n  \"userId\": \"{{user_id}}\",\n  \"amountMinorUnits\": 250,\n  \"idempotencyKey\": \"postman-debit-1\"\n}"
              }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{wallet_grpc_url}}"
            },
            "description": "Debits if balance sufficient; otherwise FAILED_PRECONDITION."
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
